# Platform Profile: Mistral

**Provider:** Mistral AI (France)  
**Current Models:** Mistral Large, Mistral Medium, Mistral 7B, Codestral  
**Interface:** chat.mistral.ai (Le Chat), API, open-weight self-hosting

---

## Strengths
- Open-weight models: full control over weights, fine-tuning, and deployment
- Strong European data sovereignty story — French company, EU data residency available
- Best-in-class French language support; strong across European languages
- Codestral: dedicated code model with strong performance
- Lightweight models (Mistral 7B) run on consumer hardware — no cloud required
- Competitive cost at API level, especially for European deployments
- Fine-tuning available on API — customize on proprietary data
- Closing the gap with proprietary frontier models on general benchmarks
- Le Chat (consumer interface) is clean and capable for everyday tasks

## Weaknesses
- Frontier model performance slightly below Claude Opus / GPT-5 on complex reasoning
- Smaller ecosystem than OpenAI or Anthropic
- Less tool integration than ChatGPT or Gemini in consumer interface
- Consumer interface (Le Chat) less feature-rich than Claude.ai or chatgpt.com

## Context Window
- Mistral Large: 128K tokens
- Mistral 7B: 32K tokens
- Behavior: Solid at long context within window limits

## Memory & Persistence
- No persistent cross-session memory in Le Chat (as of 2026)
- Self-hosted: full control over memory architecture
- Fine-tuned models: behavioral preferences baked into weights
- **Handoff note:** Include full context in prompt; for ongoing work, consider fine-tuning on use-case-specific examples

## System Prompt Support
- ✅ API: full system prompt support
- ✅ Self-hosted: full configuration control
- ✅ Le Chat: system prompt available in some configurations
- Open-weight: system prompt is your primary behavioral control surface

## Tool Availability
- Web search (Le Chat — limited)
- Code execution (Le Chat)
- API: function calling
- Self-hosted: any tool integrable via custom implementation
- Codestral: specialized for code completion in IDEs (via API)

## Prompt Format Conventions
- Follows standard chat conventions similar to Claude and ChatGPT
- For API/self-hosted: system prompt is the primary configuration lever
- For multilingual tasks: specify the target language explicitly
- For fine-tuned models: prompt conventions will vary based on training data
- Le Chat: conversational prompts work well; markdown structure is respected

## Ideal Task Types
- European enterprise deployments with EU data residency requirements
- Privacy-sensitive work requiring on-premise or sovereign cloud deployment
- French and European language tasks
- Fine-tuning on proprietary domain data (legal, medical, financial)
- Lightweight edge deployments (Mistral 7B on device)
- Cost-sensitive API workloads at scale
- Code tasks via Codestral (competitive with larger models for code completion)
- Any use case where open-weight model access is required for compliance or control

